
1.  Export the EI you want to build into /usr/local/mgi/ei/ei_build:

    Note that exporting the EI is NOT an installation of the EI!!!
    
    cd /usr/local/mgi/ei/ei_build
    cvs export -r ei-tag -d ei-tag ei

2.  Link /usr/local/mgi/ei/ei_build/ei-tag to /usr/local/mgi/ei/ei_build/ei

    rm -rf ei	(remove existing link)
    ln -s ei-tag ei

3.  Edit Configuration file:

    cd ei-tag
    cp Configuration.default Configuration
    edit Configuration file carefully and appropriately

    on rohan (development):
	setenv EIINSTALLDIR /usr/local/mgi/ei/dev
	setenv USERLOG  $HOME/.eidev-log
	setenv DSQUERY DEV_MGI
	setenv MGD mgd_release
	setenv NOMEN nomen_release

    on shire (production):
	use defaults

4.  Building

    note: install also does a build.  so, if you're ultimate
    goal is to install the application, you can skip this step.

    one application:

    	buildapp mgd compiled

    all applications:

    	buildall compiled

    For production and integration/beta testing, install compiled.
    For debugging, leave off "compiled" option.

5.  Installing

    one application:

    	installapp mgd compiled

    all applications:

    	installall compiled

    For production and integration/beta testing, install compiled.
    For debugging, leave off "compiled" option.

6.  Running:

    rohan:
    	/usr/local/mgi/ei/dev/runapp mgi

    shire:
    	/usr/local/mgi/ei/prod/runapp mgi

